Rule.Name: EnableFormsRequireSSL
Rule.Description: Verify that the requireSSL attribute on the system.web.authentication.forms configuration element is set to true which forces the authentication cookie to specify the secure attribute. This indicates the browser to only provide the cookie over SSL.
Rule.Resolution: Always enable requireSSL attribute in <forms> element. Set requireSSL to "true". This is recommended for all authentication modes, including Windows and None, since it is possible to create auth tickets manually. in unit Microsoft.OutlookApps.FaceBookings

Rule.Name: EnableHttpCookiesRequireSsl
Rule.Description: Verify that the system.web.httpCookies requireSSL configuration is set to true which forces all cookies to be sent with the secure attribute. This indicates the browser to only provide the cookie over SSL.
Rule.Resolution: Always enable requireSSL attribute in <httpCookies> element. Set requireSSL attribute to "true" in unit Microsoft.OutlookApps.FaceBookings

Rule.Name: SetViewStateUserKey
Rule.Description: Verify that the viewstate user key is set in OnInit or PageInit function. Setting the user key to a session ID or user ID prevents cross-site request forgery attacks.
Rule.Resolution: Set ViewStateUserKey property in OnInit or Page_Init function. No override for either the OnInit or Page_Init function was found. in type Microsoft.OutlookApps.FaceBookings.Default
